abstract: Rupert Murdoch’s 21st Century Fox withdrew its offer to acquire Time Warner. | Sprint and its corporate parent have ended their pursuit of T-Mobile US. | Standard Chartered is again under scrutiny. | Walgreen said on Wednesday that it would acquire the 55 percent of the British pharmacy chain Alliance Boots that it did not already own.

headline.main: Morning Agenda: Fox Gives Up on Time Warner Deal
